    "phi_err_odd": 8.572900239672832e-06,
    "D_err_-u_out_vs_+u_in": 0.0,
    "plain": "Single solution with u*>0 has TWO radial sides: one toward increasing phi, one decreasing. O4 pinch is on the increasing-phi side. The -u outward run is the decreasing-phi side of an oppositely oriented seed \u2014 related by r-reflection of the SAME local jet only if D is even and phi odd; check errors."
